 the framework does without it (degradation behavior), and when to implement it.\\n\\n7. **Transcript format guide** — How to implement transcript storage/analysis for common formats (JSONL, JSON, custom). Reference chunking helpers.\\n\\n8. **Hook installation patterns** — How to write `InstallHooks` for JSON config files (Claude pattern) and other formats.\\n\\n9. **Testing patterns** — How to write unit tests for ParseHookEvent, transcript analysis, and hook installation. Reference existing test files.\\n\\n10. **Common pitfalls** — Extracted from the codebase: go-git bugs, repo root vs cwd, transcript flush timing, nil event return pattern.\\n\\n## Key source files to reference\\n\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go` — Core + optional interfaces\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/event.go` — Event types, Event struct, ReadAndParseHookInput helper\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` — Registration pattern\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/chunking.go` — Transcript chunking helpers (ChunkJSONL, ReassembleJSONL)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/types.go` — TokenUsage, HookInput (legacy)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/` — Reference implementation (full-featured)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/` — Reference implementation (simpler, no subagents)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — Dispatcher (what framework does with events)\\n- `cmd/entire/cli/hook_registry.go` — How hooks are wired to commands\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n- Review that all interface methods are documented with correct signatures\\n- Cross-check against `agent.go` for completeness\\n- Ensure code template compiles (signatures match interfaces)\\n- Check that event mapping table covers all 7 event types\\n\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"da24e024-4b75-4a71-81c8-6a5cda3c38c0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"ab3ad40b-70c6-419c-8691-8ec4870cd9bb\",\"version\":\"2.1.37\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"rustling-doodling-treasure\",\"message\":{\"m