ing, metadata generation). The flow is:\\n     6→\\n     7→```\\n     8→Agent hook invocation → ParseHookEvent() → Event → DispatchLifecycleEvent() → framework actions\\n     9→```\\n    10→\\n    11→An agent never calls strategy methods or manages session state directly. It only answers questions: \\\"What event just happened?\\\" and \\\"What does the transcript say?\\\"\\n    12→\\n    13→## Quick Reference\\n    14→\\n    15→### Core Interface (`Agent`)\\n    16→\\n    17→Every agent must implement these 10 methods:\\n    18→\\n    19→| Group | Method | Purpose |\\n    20→|-------|--------|---------|\\n    21→| **Identity** | `Name()` | Registry key (e.g., `\\\"claude-code\\\"`) |\\n    22→| | `Type()` | Display name for metadata (e.g., `\\\"Claude Code\\\"`) |\\n    23→| | `Description()` | Human-readable description for UI |\\n    24→| | `DetectPresence()` | Check if agent is configured in the repo |\\n    25→| | `ProtectedDirs()` | Directories to preserve during rewind |\\n    26→| **Event Mapping** | `HookNames()` | Hook verbs that become CLI subcommands |\\n    27→| | `ParseHookEvent()` | **Core contribution surface** - translate native hooks to Events |\\n    28→| **Transcript** | `ReadTranscript()` | Read raw transcript bytes |\\n    29→| | `ChunkTranscript()` | Split large transcripts at format-aware boundaries |\\n    30→| | `ReassembleTranscript()` | Recombine chunks into a single transcript |\\n    31→\\n    32→### Optional Interfaces\\n    33→\\n    34→| Interface | Methods | When to implement |\\n    35→|-----------|---------|-------------------|\\n    36→| `HookSupport` | `InstallHooks`, `UninstallHooks`, `AreHooksInstalled`, `GetSupportedHooks` | Agent uses a config file for hook registration (e.g., `settings.json`) |\\n    37→| `HookHandler` | `GetHookNames` | Backward compat - delegates to `HookNames()` |\\n    38→| `TranscriptAnalyzer` | `GetTranscriptPosition`, `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset`, `ExtractPrompts`, `ExtractSummary` | You want richer checkpoints with transcript-derived file lists and prompts |\\n    39→| `TranscriptPreparer` | `PrepareTranscript` | Agent writes transcripts asynchronously and needs a flush/sync step |\\n    40→| `TokenCalculator` | `CalculateTokenUsage` | Agent's transcript contains token usage data |\\n    41→| `SubagentAwareExtractor` | `ExtractAllModifiedFiles`, `CalculateTotalTokenUsage` | Agent spawns subagents (like Claude Code's Task tool) |\\n    42→| `FileWatcher` | `GetWatchPaths`, `OnFileChange` | Agent doesn't support hooks; uses file-based detection instead |\\n    43→\\n    44→### Legacy Methods (on core `Agent`)\\n    45→\\n    46→These 8 methods are on the core interface for backward compatibility and will move to optional interfaces in a future phase. New agents should implement them as stubs that return zero values or errors:\\n    47→\\n    48→`GetHookConfigPath`, `SupportsHooks`, `ParseHookInput`, `GetSessionID`, `GetSessionDir`, `ResolveSessionFile`, `ReadSession`, `WriteSession`, `FormatResumeCommand`\\n    49→\\n    50→## Step-by-Step Implementation Guide\\n    51→\\n    52→### Step 1: Create Package\\n    53→\\n    54→Create a new directory under `cmd/entire/cli/agent/`:\\n    55→\\n    56→```\\n    57→cmd/entire/cli/agent/youragent/\\n    58→├── youragent.go          # Core Agent implementation + init()\\n    59→├── lifecycle.go          # ParseHookEvent + compile-time assertions\\n    60→├── types.go              # Hook input structs, transcript types, tool constants\\n    61→├── hooks.go              # HookSupport implementation (if applicable)\\n    62→├── transcript.go         # TranscriptAnalyzer implementation (if applicable)\\n    63→├── lifecycle_test.go     # Tests for ParseHookEvent\\n    64→├── hooks_test.go         # Tests for hook installation\\n    65→└── transcript_test.go    # Tests for transcript analysis\\n    66→```\\n    67→\\n    68→### Step 2: Define Types (`types.go`)\\n    69→\\n    70→Define structs matching your agent's native hook JSON payloads:\\n    71→\\n    72→```go\\n    73→package youragent\\n    74→\\n    75→import \\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n    76→\\n    77→// Settings file structure (for HookSupport)\\n    78→type YourAgentSettings struct {\\n    79→    Hooks YourAgentHooks `json:\\\"hooks\\\"`\\n    80→}\\n    81→\\n    82→type YourAgentHooks struct {\\n    83→    SessionStart []HookMatcher `json:\\\"SessionStart,omitempty\\\"`\\n    84→    SessionEnd   []HookMatcher `json:\\\"SessionEnd,omitempty\\\"`\\n    85→    // ... other hook types your agent supports\\n    86→}\\n    87→\\n    88→type HookMatcher struct {\\n    89→    Matcher string      `json:\\\"matcher,omitempty\\\"`\\n    90→    Hooks   []HookEntry `json:\\\"hooks\\\"`\\n    91→}\\n    92→\\n    93→type HookEntry struct {\\n    94→    Type    string `json:\\\"type\\\"`\\n    95→    Command string `json:\\\"command\\\"`\\n    96→}\\n    97→\\n    98→// Hook input structs - match your agent's JSON payloads\\n    99→\\n   100→type sessionInfoRaw struct {\\n   101→    SessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n   102→    TranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n   103→}\\n   104→\\n   105→type promptInputRaw struct {\\n   106→    SessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n   107→    TranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n   108→    Prompt         string `json:\\\"prompt\\\"`\\n   109→}\\n   110→\\n   111→// Tool constants - tools in your agent that modify files\\n   112→const (\\n   113→    ToolWrite = \\\"write_file\\\"\\n   114→    ToolEdit  = \\\"edit_file\\\"\\n   115→)\\n   116→\\n   117→var FileModificationTools = []string{ToolWrite, ToolEdit}\\n   118→```\\n   119→\\n   120→### Step 3: Implement Core Agent Interface (`youragent.go`)\\n   121→\\n   122→```go\\n   123→package youragent\\n   124→\\n   125→import (\\n   126→    \\\"errors\\\"\\n   127→    \\\"fmt\\\"\\n   128→    \\\"io\\\"\\n   129→    \\\"os\\\"\\n   130→    \\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n   131→    \\\"time\\\"\\n   132→\\n   133→    \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n   134→    \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths\\\"\\n   135→)\\n   136→\\n   137→//nolint:gochecknoinits // Agent self-registration is the intended pattern\\n   138→func init() {\\n   139→    agent.Register(\\\"your-agent\\\", NewYourAgent)\\n   140→}\\n   141→\\n   142→type YourAgent struct{}\\n   143→\\n   144→func NewYourAgent() agent.Agent {\\n   145→    return &YourAgent{}\\n   146→}\\n   147→\\n   148→// --- Identity ---\\n   149→\\n   150→func (a *YourAgent) Name() agent.AgentName    { return \\\"your-agent\\\" }\\n   151→func (a *YourAgent) Type() agent.AgentType     { return \\\"Your Agent\\\" }\\n   152→func (a *YourAgent) Description() string       { return \\\"Your Agent - description here\\\" }\\n   153→func (a *YourAgent) ProtectedDirs() []string   { return []string{\\\".youragent\\\"} }\\n   154→\\n   155→func (a *YourAgent) DetectPresence() (bool, error) {\\n   156→    repoRoot, err := paths.RepoRoot()\\n   157→    if err != nil {\\n   158→        repoRoot = \\\".\\\"\\n   159→    }\\n   160→    _, err = os.Stat(filepath.Join(repoRoot, \\\".youragent\\\"))\\n   161→    if err == nil {\\n   162→        return true, nil\\n   163→    }\\n   164→    return false, nil\\n   165→}\\n   166→\\n   167→// --- Transcript Storage ---\\n   168→\\n   169→func (a *YourAgent) ReadTranscript(sessionRef string) ([]byte, error) {\\n   170→    data, err := os.ReadFile(sessionRef)\\n   171→    if err != nil {\\n   172→        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to read transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n   173→    }\\n   174→    return data, nil\\n   175→}\\n   176→\\n   177→func (a *YourAgent) ChunkTranscript(content []byte, maxSize int) ([][]byte, error) {\\n   178→    // Use JSONL chunking for line-based formats\\n   179→    return agent.ChunkJSONL(content, maxSize)\\n   180→    // Or implement format-specific chunking (see geminicli for JSON example)\\n   181→}\\n   182→\\n   183→func (a *YourAgent) ReassembleTranscript(chunks [][]byte) ([]byte, error) {\\n   184→    return agent.ReassembleJSONL(chunks), nil\\n   185→}\\n   186→\\n   187→// --- Legacy stubs (required by interface, will be removed in future) ---\\n   188→\\n   189→func (a *YourAgent) GetHookConfigPath() string                     { return \\\".youragent/settings.json\\\" }\\n   190→func (a *YourAgent) SupportsHooks() bool                           { return true }\\n   191→func (a *YourAgent) GetSessionID(input *agent.HookInput) string    { return input.SessionID }\\n   192→func (a *YourAgent) FormatResumeCommand(sessionID string) string   { return \\\"youragent --resume \\\" + sessionID }\\n   193→\\n   194→func (a *YourAgent) ParseHookInput(_ agent.HookType, _ io.Reader) (*agent.HookInput, error) {\\n   195→    return nil, errors.New(\\\"use ParseHookEvent instead\\\")\\n   196→}\\n   197→\\n   198→func (a *YourAgent) GetSessionDir(_ string) (string, error) {\\n   199→    return \\\"\\\", errors.New(\\\"not implemented\\\")\\n   200→}\\n   201→\\n   202→func (a *YourAgent) ResolveSessionFile(sessionDir, agentSessionID string) string {\\n   203→    return filepath.Join(sessionDir, agentSessionID+\\\".jsonl\\\")\\n   204→}\\n   205→\\n   206→func (a *YourAgent) ReadSession(_ *agent.HookInput) (*agent.AgentSession, error) {\\n   207→    return nil, errors.New(\\\"not implemented\\\")\\n   208→}\\n   209→\\n   210→func (a *YourAgent) WriteSession(_ *agent.AgentSession) error {\\n   211→    return errors.New(\\\"not implemented\\\")\\n   212→}\\n   213→```\\n   214→\\n   215→### Step 4: Implement `ParseHookEvent` (`lifecycle.go`)\\n   216→\\n   217→This is the **main contribution surface** for new agents. Map each of your agent's native hook names to the normalized `EventType`:\\n   218→\\n   219→```go\\n   220→package youragent\\n   221→\\n   222→import (\\n   223→    \\\"io\\\"\\n   224→    \\\"time\\\"\\n   225→\\n   226→    \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n   227→)\\n   228→\\n   229→// Hook name constants - these become CLI subcommands\\n   230→const (\\n   231→    HookNameSessionStart = \\\"session-start\\\"\\n   232→    HookNameSessionEnd   = \\\"session-end\\\"\\n   233→    HookNamePromptSubmit = \\\"prompt-submit\\\"\\n   234→    HookNameResponse     = \\\"response\\\"\\n   235→)\\n   236→\\n   237→func (a *YourAgent) HookNames() []string {\\n   238→    return []string{\\n   239→        HookNameSessionStart,\\n   240→        HookNameSessionEnd,\\n   241→        HookNamePromptSubmit,\\n   242→        HookNameResponse,\\n   243→    }\\n   244→}\\n   245→\\n   246→func (a *YourAgent) ParseHookEvent(hookName string, stdin io.Reader) (*agent.Event, error) {\\n   247→    switch hookName {\\n   248→    case HookNameSessionStart:\\n   249→        raw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](stdin)\\n   250→        if err != nil {\\n   251→            return nil, err\\n   252→        }\\n   253→        return &agent.Event{\\n   254→            Type:       agent.SessionStart,\\n   255→            SessionID:  raw.SessionID,\\n   256→            SessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath,\\n   257→            Timestamp:  time.Now(),\\n   258→        }, nil\\n   259→\\n   260→    case HookNamePromptSubmit:\\n   261→        raw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[promptInputRaw](stdin)\\n   262→        if err != nil {\\n   263→            return nil, err\\n   264→        }\\n   265→        return &agent.Event{\\n   266→            Type:       agent.TurnStart,\\n   267→            SessionID:  raw.SessionID,\\n   268→            SessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath,\\n   269→            Prompt:     raw.Prompt,\\n   270→            Timestamp:  time.Now(),\\n   271→        }, nil\\n   272→\\n   273→    case HookNameResponse:\\n   274→        raw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](stdin)\\n   275→        if err != nil {\\n   276→            return nil, err\\n   277→        }\\n   278→        return &agent.Event{\\n   279→            Type:       agent.TurnEnd,\\n   280→            SessionID:  raw.SessionID,\\n   281→            SessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath,\\n   282→            Timestamp:  time.Now(),\\n   283→        }, nil\\n   284→\\n   285→    case HookNameSessionEnd:\\n   286→        raw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](stdin)\\n   287→        if err != nil {\\n   288→            return nil, err\\n   289→        }\\n   290→        return &agent.Event{\\n   291→            Type:       agent.SessionEnd,\\n   292→            SessionID:  raw.SessionID,\\n   293→            SessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath,\\n   294→            Timestamp:  time.Now(),\\n   295→        }, nil\\n   296→\\n   297→    default:\\n   298→        // Unknown hooks have no lifecycle significance\\n   299→        return nil, nil //nolint:nilnil\\n   300→    }\\n   301→}\\n   302→```\\n   303→\\n   304→Key decisions in `ParseHookEvent`:\\n   305→\\n   306→- **Return `nil, nil`** for hooks with no lifecycle significance (pass-through hooks). This is not an error - it tells the framework to do nothing.\\n   307→- **Every event must have `SessionID` and `SessionRef`**. The framework validates these.\\n   308→- **`TurnStart` should include `Prompt`** if available - it's used for commit message generation.\\n   309→- **Use `agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[T]`** - the generic helper reads stdin and unmarshals JSON in one step.\\n   310→- **Set `Timestamp` to `time.Now()`** - the framework uses this for ordering.\\n   311→\\n   312→### Step 5: Choose and Implement Optional Interfaces\\n   313→\\n   314→See the [Optional Interface Decision Tree](#optional-interface-decision-tree) section below.\\n   315→\\n   316→### Step 6: Register via `init()`\\n   317→\\n   318→Registration happens in `init()` in your main agent file. The import side-effect pattern ensures your agent is available when the CLI starts:\\n   319→\\n   320→```go\\n   321→//nolint:gochecknoinits // Agent self-registration is the intended pattern\\n   322→func init() {\\n   323→    agent.Register(\\\"your-agent\\\", NewYourAgent)\\n   324→}\\n   325→```\\n   326→\\n   327→Then add a blank import in the CLI's command setup to ensure the package is loaded:\\n   328→\\n   329→```go\\n   330→// In cmd/entire/cli/commands/ or wherever agents are imported\\n   331→import (\\n   332→    _ \\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/youragent\\\"\\n   333→)\\n   334→```\\n   335→\\n   336→### Step 7: Add Compile-Time Interface Assertions\\n   337→\\n   338→In `lifecycle.go` (or whichever file implements the optional interfaces), add compile-time checks:\\n   339→\\n   340→```go\\n   341→// Compile-time interface assertions\\n   342→var (\\n   343→    _ agent.TranscriptAnalyzer = (*YourAgent)(nil)\\n   344→    _ agent.TokenCalculator    = (*YourAgent)(nil)\\n   345→    // Add one line per optional interface you implement\\n   346→)\\n   347→```\\n   348→\\n   349→Also add assertions for `HookSupport` and `HookHandler` in `hooks.go` if applicable:\\n   350→\\n   351→```go\\n   352→var (\\n   353→    _ agent.HookSupport = (*YourAgent)(nil)\\n   354→    _ agent.HookHandler = (*YourAgent)(nil)\\n   355→)\\n   356→```\\n   357→\\n   358→### Step 8: Implement Hook Installation (if `HookSupport`)\\n   359→\\n   360→If your agent uses a JSON config file for hooks (like Claude Code's `.claude/settings.json` or Gemini's `.gemini/settings.json`), implement `HookSupport`:\\n   361→\\n   362→```go\\n   363→func (a *YourAgent) InstallHooks(localDev bool, force bool) (int, error) {\\n   364→    // 1. Find repo root\\n   365→    repoRoot, err := paths.RepoRoot()\\n   366→    if err != nil {\\n   367→        return 0, err\\n   368→    }\\n   369→\\n   370→    // 2. Read existing settings (preserve unknown fields)\\n   371→    settingsPath := filepath.Join(repoRoot, \\\".youragent\\\", \\\"settings.json\\\")\\n   372→    // ... read and parse ...\\n   373→\\n   374→    // 3. Build hook commands\\n   375→    var cmdPrefix string\\n   376→    if localDev {\\n   377→        cmdPrefix = \\\"go run ${PROJECT_DIR}/cmd/entire/main.go hooks your-agent \\\"\\n   378→    } else {\\n   379→        cmdPrefix = \\\"entire hooks your-agent \\\"\\n   380→    }\\n   381→\\n   382→    // 4. Add hooks if they don't exist (idempotent)\\n   383→    // 5. Write settings back (preserving unknown fields)\\n   384→\\n   385→    return count, nil\\n   386→}\\n   387→\\n   388→func (a *YourAgent) UninstallHooks() error         { /* reverse of install */ }\\n   389→func (a *YourAgent) AreHooksInstalled() bool        { /* check settings file */ }\\n   390→func (a *YourAgent) GetSupportedHooks() []agent.HookType { /* list supported types */ }\\n   391→```\\n   392→\\n   393→Also implement `HookHandler` for backward compatibility:\\n   394→\\n   395→```go\\n   396→func (a *YourAgent) GetHookNames() []string {\\n   397→    return a.HookNames() // delegate to the core interface method\\n   398→}\\n   399→```\\n   400→\\n   401→### Step 9: Write Tests\\n   402→\\n   403→Test `ParseHookEvent` for every hook name your agent supports. See [Testing Patterns](#testing-patterns) below.\\n   404→\\n   405→## Event Mapping Reference\\n   406→\\n   407→The framework dispatcher (`DispatchLifecycleEvent` in `lifecycle.go`) handles each event type as follows:\\n   408→\\n   409→| Event Type | Framework Actions | Claude Code Hook | Gemini CLI Hook |\\n   410→|------------|-------------------|------------------|-----------------|\\n   411→| `SessionStart` | Shows banner, checks concurrent sessions, fires state machine transition | `session-start` | `session-start` |\\n   412→| `TurnStart` | Captures pre-prompt state (git status, transcript position), ensures strategy setup, initializes session | `user-prompt-submit` | `before-agent` |\\n   413→| `TurnEnd` | Validates transcript, extracts metadata (prompts, summary, files), detects file changes via git status, saves step + checkpoint, transitions phase to IDLE | `stop` | `after-agent` |\\n   414→| `Compaction` | Fires compaction transition (stays ACTIVE), resets transcript offset | *(not used)* | `pre-compress` |\\n   415→| `SessionEnd` | Marks session as ENDED in state machine | `session-end` | `session-end` |\\n   416→| `SubagentStart` | Captures pre-task state (git status snapshot) | `pre-task` (PreToolUse[Task]) | *(not used)* |\\n   417→| `SubagentEnd` | Extracts subagent modified files, detects changes, saves task checkpoint | `post-task` (PostToolUse[Task]) | *(not used)* |\\n   418→\\n   419→### Event Field Requirements\\n   420→\\n   421→| Event Type | Required Fields | Optional Fields |\\n   422→|------------|----------------|-----------------|\\n   423→| `SessionStart` | `SessionID`, `SessionRef` | `ResponseMessage` |\\n   424→| `TurnStart` | `SessionID`, `SessionRef` | `Prompt`, `PreviousSessionID` |\\n   425→| `TurnEnd` | `SessionID`, `SessionRef` | |\\n   426→| `Compaction` | `SessionID` | `SessionRef` |\\n   427→| `SessionEnd` | `SessionID` | `SessionRef` |\\n   428→| `SubagentStart` | `SessionID`, `SessionRef`, `ToolUseID` | `ToolInput` |\\n   429→| `SubagentEnd` | `SessionID`, `SessionRef`, `ToolUseID` | `SubagentID`, `ToolInput` |\\n   430→\\n   431→## Optional Interface Decision Tree\\n   432→\\n   433→### `TranscriptAnalyzer`\\n   434→\\n   435→**What it enables:** Transcript-derived file lists (more accurate than git-status-only), extracted user prompts in checkpoint metadata, session summaries.\\n   436→\\n   437→**Without it:** The framework still creates checkpoints using git-status-based file detection and stores the raw transcript. Prompts and summary fields will be empty.\\n   438→\\n   439→**Implement when:** Your agent writes a parseable transcript (JSONL, JSON, or any structured format) and you can extract which files were modified and what the user asked.\\n   440→\\n   441→**Methods:**\\n   442→- `GetTranscriptPosition(path) (int, error)` - Return current position. For JSONL: line count. For JSON with messages array: message count.\\n   443→- `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(path, startOffset) (files, currentPosition, error)` - Parse transcript from offset and return files touched by write/edit tools.\\n   444→- `ExtractPrompts(sessionRef, fromOffset) ([]string, error)` - Extract user prompt strings.\\n   445→- `ExtractSummary(sessionRef) (string, error)` - Extract last assistant response as summary.\\n   446→\\n   447→### `TranscriptPreparer`\\n   448→\\n   449→**What it enables:** A pre-read synchronization step before the framework reads the transcript.\\n   450→\\n   451→**Without it:** The framework reads the transcript immediately, which may be incomplete if the agent writes asynchronously.\\n   452→\\n   453→**Implement when:** Your agent writes transcripts asynchronously (e.g., Claude Code uses an async writer and needs to wait for a flush sentinel before reading).\\n   454→\\n   455→**Method:**\\n   456→- `PrepareTranscript(sessionRef) error` - Wait until the transcript is fully written. Called before `ReadTranscript`.\\n   457→\\n   458→### `TokenCalculator`\\n   459→\\n   460→**What it enables:** Token usage metrics in checkpoint metadata (input, output, cache tokens, API call count).\\n   461→\\n   462→**Without it:** Token usage fields are empty in checkpoint metadata.\\n   463→\\n   464→**Implement when:** Your agent's transcript contains token/usage data per message.\\n   465→\\n   466→**Method:**\\n   467→- `CalculateTokenUsage(sessionRef, fromOffset) (*TokenUsage, error)` - Sum token usage from offset to end of transcript.\\n   468→\\n   469→### `SubagentAwareExtractor`\\n   470→\\n   471→**What it enables:** Includes files modified by spawned subagents in the checkpoint file list and aggregates subagent token usage.\\n   472→\\n   473→**Without it:** Only the main agent's transcript is analyzed. Subagent modifications are still captured by git status but not attributed to the subagent.\\n   474→\\n   475→**Implement when:** Your agent spawns subagents (task workers) that have their own transcripts.\\n   476→\\n   477→**Methods:**\\n   478→- `ExtractAllModifiedFiles(sessionRef, fromOffset, subagentsDir) ([]string, error)` - Deduplicated file list from main + subagent transcripts.\\n   479→- `CalculateTotalTokenUsage(sessionRef, fromOffset, subagentsDir) (*TokenUsage, error)` - Aggregated usage including subagents.\\n   480→\\n   481→### `HookSupport`\\n   482→\\n   483→**What it enables:** `entire enable` automatically installs hooks into the agent's config file.\\n   484→\\n   485→**Without it:** Users must manually configure hooks to call `entire hooks <agent> <verb>`.\\n   486→\\n   487→**Implement when:** Your agent supports a config file with hook definitions (e.g., `.claude/settings.json`, `.gemini/settings.json`).\\n   488→\\n   489→### `FileWatcher`\\n   490→\\n   491→**What it enables:** Detecting session activity by watching file changes instead of hooks.\\n   492→\\n   493→**Without it:** The agent must support hooks for the framework to receive events.\\n   494→\\n   495→**Implement when:** Your agent doesn't support lifecycle hooks but writes session data to predictable file paths.\\n   496→\\n   497→## Transcript Format Guide\\n   498→\\n   499→### JSONL Format (Claude Code pattern)\\n   500→\\n   501→One JSON object per line. Each line is a transcript entry (user message, assistant message, tool use, etc.):\\n   502→\\n   503→```\\n   504→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"user\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Fix the bug\\\"},\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\"}\\n   505→{\\\"type\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"message\\\":{\\\"role\\\":\\\"assistant\\\",\\\"content\\\":[...]},\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"...\\\"}\\n   506→```\\n   507→\\n   508→**Chunking:** Use `agent.ChunkJSONL(content, maxSize)` - splits at newline boundaries.\\n   509→**Reassembly:** Use `agent.ReassembleJSONL(chunks)` - concatenates with newlines.\\n   510→**Position:** Line count (`bufio.Reader` + count `\\\\n`).\\n   511→**Offset:** Start parsing at line N (skip first N lines).\\n   512→\\n   513→### JSON Format (Gemini CLI pattern)\\n   514→\\n   515→Single JSON object with a `messages` array:\\n   516→\\n   517→```json\\n   518→{\\\"messages\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"user\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"gemini\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"...\\\"}]}\\n   519→```\\n   520→\\n   521→**Chunking:** Parse the JSON, split the messages array across chunks, marshal each chunk as a complete JSON object with a subset of messages.\\n   522→**Reassembly:** Parse each chunk, concatenate all message arrays, marshal back.\\n   523→**Position:** Message count (`len(transcript.Messages)`).\\n   524→**Offset:** Start iterating messages at index N.\\n   525→\\n   526→### Using Chunking Helpers\\n   527→\\n   528→The `agent` package provides format-agnostic entry points:\\n   529→\\n   530→```go\\n   531→// These dispatch to the agent's ChunkTranscript/ReassembleTranscript methods\\n   532→agent.ChunkTranscript(content, agentType)     // agentType → agent lookup → format-aware chunking\\n   533→agent.ReassembleTranscript(chunks, agentType)  // agentType → agent lookup → format-aware reassembly\\n   534→\\n   535→// Direct JSONL helpers (usable without an agent)\\n   536→agent.ChunkJSONL(content, maxSize)\\n   537→agent.ReassembleJSONL(chunks)\\n   538→\\n   539→// Chunk file naming\\n   540→agent.ChunkFileName(\\\"full.jsonl\\\", 0)  // \\\"full.jsonl\\\"\\n   541→agent.ChunkFileName(\\\"full.jsonl\\\", 1)  // \\\"full.jsonl.001\\\"\\n   542→agent.ParseChunkIndex(\\\"full.jsonl.002\\\", \\\"full.jsonl\\\")  // 2\\n   543→agent.SortChunkFiles(files, \\\"full.jsonl\\\")  // sorted by chunk index\\n   544→```\\n   545→\\n   546→## Hook Installation Patterns\\n   547→\\n   548→### JSON Config File Pattern\\n   549→\\n   550→Both Claude Code and Gemini CLI use a JSON settings file in their config directory. The installation pattern is:\\n   551→\\n   552→1. **Read existing settings** as `map[string]json.RawMessage` to preserve unknown fields\\n   553→2. **Parse only the hook types you modify** into typed slices\\n   554→3. **Remove existing Entire hooks** (for `force` mode or mode-switching)\\n   555→4. **Add new hooks** idempotently (check if command already exists)\\n   556→5. **Marshal modified types back** to the raw map\\n   557→6. **Write the file** with pretty-printing\\n   558→\\n   559→Key principles:\\n   560→- **Preserve unknown fields** - don't destroy user's custom hooks or settings\\n   561→- **Idempotent installs** - running `entire enable` twice doesn't duplicate hooks\\n   562→- **Support `localDev` mode** - use `go run ${PROJECT_DIR}/...` for development\\n   563→- **Identify Entire hooks** by command prefix (e.g., `\\\"entire \\\"` or `\\\"go run ${...}\\\"`)\\n   564→\\n   565→### Example: Claude Code Hook Config\\n   566→\\n   567→```json\\n   568→{\\n   569→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n   570→    \\\"SessionStart\\\": [{\\\"matcher\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks claude-code session-start\\\"}]}],\\n   571→    \\\"Stop\\\": [{\\\"matcher\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks claude-code stop\\\"}]}],\\n   572→    \\\"PreToolUse\\\": [{\\\"matcher\\\": \\\"Task\\\", \\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks claude-code pre-task\\\"}]}]\\n   573→  }\\n   574→}\\n   575→```\\n   576→\\n   577→### Example: Gemini CLI Hook Config\\n   578→\\n   579→```json\\n   580→{\\n   581→  \\\"hooksConfig\\\": {\\\"enabled\\\": true},\\n   582→  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n   583→    \\\"SessionStart\\\": [{\\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"entire-session-start\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks gemini session-start\\\"}]}],\\n   584→    \\\"AfterAgent\\\": [{\\\"hooks\\\": [{\\\"name\\\": \\\"entire-after-agent\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"command\\\", \\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks gemini after-agent\\\"}]}]\\n   585→  }\\n   586→}\\n   587→```\\n   588→\\n   589→Note: Gemini CLI requires `hooksConfig.enabled: true` and each hook entry requires a `name` field.\\n   590→\\n   591→## Testing Patterns\\n   592→\\n   593→### Testing `ParseHookEvent`\\n   594→\\n   595→Test every hook name, including pass-through hooks that return nil:\\n   596→\\n   597→```go\\n   598→func TestParseHookEvent_TurnStart(t *testing.T) {\\n   599→    t.Parallel()\\n   600→\\n   601→    ag := &YourAgent{}\\n   602→    input := `{\\\"session_id\\\": \\\"sess-123\\\", \\\"transcript_path\\\": \\\"/tmp/t.jsonl\\\", \\\"prompt\\\": \\\"Fix the bug\\\"}`\\n   603→\\n   604→    event, err := ag.ParseHookEvent(HookNamePromptSubmit, strings.NewReader(input))\\n   605→\\n   606→    if err != nil {\\n   607→        t.Fatalf(\\\"unexpected error: %v\\\", err)\\n   608→    }\\n   609→    if event == nil {\\n   610→        t.Fatal(\\\"expected event, got nil\\\")\\n   611→    }\\n   612→    if event.Type != agent.TurnStart {\\n   613→        t.Errorf(\\\"expected TurnStart, got %v\\\", event.Type)\\n   614→    }\\n   615→    if event.Prompt != \\\"Fix the bug\\\" {\\n   616→        t.Errorf(\\\"expected prompt 'Fix the bug', got %q\\\", event.Prompt)\\n   617→    }\\n   618→}\\n   619→```\\n   620→\\n   621→### Testing Nil Returns\\n   622→\\n   623→Hooks with no lifecycle action must return `nil, nil`:\\n   624→\\n   625→```go\\n   626→func TestParseHookEvent_PassThrough_ReturnsNil(t *testing.T) {\\n   627→    t.Parallel()\\n   628→\\n   629→    ag := &YourAgent{}\\n   630→    event, err := ag.ParseHookEvent(\\\"some-pass-through-hook\\\", strings.NewReader(`{}`))\\n   631→\\n   632→    if err != nil {\\n   633→        t.Fatalf(\\\"unexpected error: %v\\\", err)\\n   634→    }\\n   635→    if event != nil {\\n   636→        t.Errorf(\\\"expected nil event, got %+v\\\", event)\\n   637→    }\\n   638→}\\n   639→```\\n   640→\\n   641→### Testing Error Cases\\n   642→\\n   643→```go\\n   644→func TestParseHookEvent_EmptyInput(t *testing.T) {\\n   645→    t.Parallel()\\n   646→\\n   647→    ag := &YourAgent{}\\n   648→    _, err := ag.ParseHookEvent(HookNameSessionStart, strings.NewReader(\\\"\\\"))\\n   649→\\n   650→    if err == nil {\\n   651→        t.Fatal(\\\"expected error for empty input\\\")\\n   652→    }\\n   653→    if !strings.Contains(err.Error(), \\\"empty hook input\\\") {\\n   654→        t.Errorf(\\\"expected 'empty hook input' error, got: %v\\\", err)\\n   655→    }\\n   656→}\\n   657→\\n   658→func TestParseHookEvent_MalformedJSON(t *testing.T) {\\n   659→    t.Parallel()\\n   660→\\n   661→    ag := &YourAgent{}\\n   662→    _, err := ag.ParseHookEvent(HookNameSessionStart, strings.NewReader(\\\"not json\\\"))\\n   663→\\n   664→    if err == nil {\\n   665→        t.Fatal(\\\"expected error for malformed JSON\\\")\\n   666→    }\\n   667→}\\n   668→```\\n   669→\\n   670→### Testing Hook Installation\\n   671→\\n   672→```go\\n   673→func TestInstallHooks_CreatesSettingsFile(t *testing.T) {\\n   674→    t.Parallel()\\n   675→\\n   676→    dir := t.TempDir()\\n   677→    // ... set up test repo, create .youragent/ directory ...\\n   678→\\n   679→    ag := &YourAgent{}\\n   680→    count, err := ag.InstallHooks(false, false)\\n   681→\\n   682→    if err != nil {\\n   683→        t.Fatalf(\\\"unexpected error: %v\\\", err)\\n   684→    }\\n   685→    if count == 0 {\\n   686→        t.Error(\\\"expected hooks to be installed\\\")\\n   687→    }\\n   688→\\n   689→    // Verify settings file was created and contains hooks\\n   690→    data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(dir, \\\".youragent\\\", \\\"settings.json\\\"))\\n   691→    // ... assert hooks are present ...\\n   692→}\\n   693→\\n   694→func TestInstallHooks_Idempotent(t *testing.T) {\\n   695→    t.Parallel()\\n   696→\\n   697→    // Install twice, second call should return count=0\\n   698→    ag := &YourAgent{}\\n   699→    ag.InstallHooks(false, false)\\n   700→    count, _ := ag.InstallHooks(false, false)\\n   701→    if count != 0 {\\n   702→        t.Errorf(\\\"expected 0 new hooks on second install, got %d\\\", count)\\n   703→    }\\n   704→}\\n   705→```\\n   706→\\n   707→### Test file references\\n   708→\\n   709→- Claude Code lifecycle tests: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle_test.go`\\n   710→- Claude Code hooks tests: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/hooks_test.go`\\n   711→- Claude Code transcript tests: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/transcript_test.go`\\n   712→- Gemini CLI lifecycle tests: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle_test.go`\\n   713→- Gemini CLI hooks tests: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/hooks_test.go`\\n   714→- Gemini CLI transcript tests: `cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript_test.go`\\n   715→\\n   716→## Common Pitfalls\\n   717→\\n   718→### go-git v5 Bugs\\n   719→\\n   720→**Do NOT use go-git v5 for `checkout` or `reset --hard` operations.** go-git v5 has a bug where `worktree.Reset()` with `HardReset` and `worktree.Checkout()` incorrectly delete untracked directories even when listed in `.gitignore`. This would destroy `.entire/` and agent config directories. Use the git CLI instead. See `CLAUDE.md` for details and `hard_reset_test.go` for regression tests.\\n   721→\\n   722→### Repo Root vs Current Working Directory\\n   723→\\n   724→Git commands return paths relative to the **repository root**, not the current working directory. When your code runs from a subdirectory, `os.Getwd()` gives wrong results for path construction. Always use `paths.RepoRoot()`:\\n   725→\\n   726→```go\\n   727→// WRONG\\n   728→cwd, _ := os.Getwd()\\n   729→absPath := filepath.Join(cwd, file) // Breaks from subdirectory\\n   730→\\n   731→// CORRECT\\n   732→repoRoot, _ := paths.RepoRoot()\\n   733→absPath := filepath.Join(repoRoot, file)\\n   734→```\\n   735→\\n   736→### Transcript Flush Timing\\n   737→\\n   738→Some agents write transcripts asynchronously. If `ReadTranscript` is called before the write completes, the transcript will be incomplete. Implement `TranscriptPreparer` if your agent has this behavior. Claude Code solves this by writing a sentinel entry and polling for it (see `waitForTranscriptFlush` in `claudecode/lifecycle.go`).\\n   739→\\n   740→### Nil Event Return Pattern\\n   741→\\n   742→`ParseHookEvent` returning `(nil, nil)` is **not an error** - it means the hook has no lifecycle significance. The framework (in `hook_registry.go`) checks:\\n   743→\\n   744→```go\\n   745→event, parseErr := ag.ParseHookEvent(hookName, stdin)\\n   746→if event != nil {\\n   747→    hookErr = DispatchLifecycleEvent(ag, event)\\n   748→}\\n   749→// nil event → no-op (hook is silently acknowledged)\\n   750→```\\n   751→\\n   752→Use `//nolint:nilnil` to suppress the linter warning on intentional nil returns.\\n   753→\\n   754→### Agent Name vs Agent Type\\n   755→\\n   756→- `AgentName` is the **registry key** used in code (`\\\"claude-code\\\"`, `\\\"gemini\\\"`). It appears in CLI commands: `entire hooks claude-code stop`.\\n   757→- `AgentType` is the **display name** stored in metadata and commit trailers (`\\\"Claude Code\\\"`, `\\\"Gemini CLI\\\"`). It's what users see.\\n   758→\\n   759→Register constants for both in `cmd/entire/cli/agent/registry.go` when adding a new agent.\\n   760→\\n   761→### Hook Names as CLI Subcommands\\n   762→\\n   763→The strings returned by `HookNames()` become literal CLI subcommands under `entire hooks <agent>`. For example, if `HookNames()` returns `[\\\"session-start\\\", \\\"stop\\\"]`, the CLI creates:\\n   764→- `entire hooks your-agent session-start`\\n   765→- `entire hooks your-agent stop`\\n   766→\\n   767→These commands read JSON from stdin and dispatch to `ParseHookEvent`. The agent's hook config should invoke these commands.\\n   768→\\n   769→## Complete Code Template\\n   770→\\n   771→A minimal but functional agent skeleton. Copy this directory structure and fill in agent-specific details:\\n   772→\\n   773→<details>\\n   774→<summary>youragent/types.go</summary>\\n   775→\\n   776→```go\\n   777→package youragent\\n   778→\\n   779→// sessionInfoRaw matches your agent's session hook JSON payload.\\n   780→type sessionInfoRaw struct {\\n   781→\\tSessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n   782→\\tTranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n   783→}\\n   784→\\n   785→// promptInputRaw matches your agent's prompt-submit hook JSON payload.\\n   786→type promptInputRaw struct {\\n   787→\\tSessionID      string `json:\\\"session_id\\\"`\\n   788→\\tTranscriptPath string `json:\\\"transcript_path\\\"`\\n   789→\\tPrompt         string `json:\\\"prompt\\\"`\\n   790→}\\n   791→```\\n   792→\\n   793→</details>\\n   794→\\n   795→<details>\\n   796→<summary>youragent/youragent.go</summary>\\n   797→\\n   798→```go\\n   799→package youragent\\n   800→\\n   801→import (\\n   802→\\t\\\"errors\\\"\\n   803→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n   804→\\t\\\"io\\\"\\n   805→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n   806→\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n   807→\\n   808→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n   809→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/paths\\\"\\n   810→)\\n   811→\\n   812→//nolint:gochecknoinits // Agent self-registration is the intended pattern\\n   813→func init() {\\n   814→\\tagent.Register(\\\"your-agent\\\", NewYourAgent)\\n   815→}\\n   816→\\n   817→type YourAgent struct{}\\n   818→\\n   819→func NewYourAgent() agent.Agent { return &YourAgent{} }\\n   820→\\n   821→func (a *YourAgent) Name() agent.AgentName  { return \\\"your-agent\\\" }\\n   822→func (a *YourAgent) Type() agent.AgentType   { return \\\"Your Agent\\\" }\\n   823→func (a *YourAgent) Description() string     { return \\\"Your Agent - brief description\\\" }\\n   824→func (a *YourAgent) ProtectedDirs() []string { return []string{\\\".youragent\\\"} }\\n   825→\\n   826→func (a *YourAgent) DetectPresence() (bool, error) {\\n   827→\\trepoRoot, err := paths.RepoRoot()\\n   828→\\tif err != nil {\\n   829→\\t\\trepoRoot = \\\".\\\"\\n   830→\\t}\\n   831→\\tif _, err := os.Stat(filepath.Join(repoRoot, \\\".youragent\\\")); err == nil {\\n   832→\\t\\treturn true, nil\\n   833→\\t}\\n   834→\\treturn false, nil\\n   835→}\\n   836→\\n   837→func (a *YourAgent) ReadTranscript(sessionRef string) ([]byte, error) {\\n   838→\\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(sessionRef) //nolint:gosec // Path from agent hook\\n   839→\\tif err != nil {\\n   840→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to read transcript: %w\\\", err)\\n   841→\\t}\\n   842→\\treturn data, nil\\n   843→}\\n   844→\\n   845→func (a *YourAgent) ChunkTranscript(content []byte, maxSize int) ([][]byte, error) {\\n   846→\\treturn agent.ChunkJSONL(content, maxSize)\\n   847→}\\n   848→\\n   849→func (a *YourAgent) ReassembleTranscript(chunks [][]byte) ([]byte, error) {\\n   850→\\treturn agent.ReassembleJSONL(chunks), nil\\n   851→}\\n   852→\\n   853→// --- Legacy stubs ---\\n   854→func (a *YourAgent) GetHookConfigPath() string                                          { return \\\"\\\" }\\n   855→func (a *YourAgent) SupportsHooks() bool                                                { return true }\\n   856→func (a *YourAgent) ParseHookInput(_ agent.HookType, _ io.Reader) (*agent.HookInput, error) { return nil, errors.New(\\\"use ParseHookEvent\\\") }\\n   857→func (a *YourAgent) GetSessionID(input *agent.HookInput) string                         { return input.SessionID }\\n   858→func (a *YourAgent) GetSessionDir(_ string) (string, error)                             { return \\\"\\\", errors.New(\\\"not implemented\\\") }\\n   859→func (a *YourAgent) ResolveSessionFile(dir, id string) string                           { return filepath.Join(dir, id+\\\".jsonl\\\") }\\n   860→func (a *YourAgent) ReadSession(_ *agent.HookInput) (*agent.AgentSession, error)        { return nil, errors.New(\\\"not implemented\\\") }\\n   861→func (a *YourAgent) WriteSession(_ *agent.AgentSession) error                           { return errors.New(\\\"not implemented\\\") }\\n   862→func (a *YourAgent) FormatResumeCommand(id string) string                               { return \\\"youragent --resume \\\" + id }\\n   863→```\\n   864→\\n   865→</details>\\n   866→\\n   867→<details>\\n   868→<summary>youragent/lifecycle.go</summary>\\n   869→\\n   870→```go\\n   871→package youragent\\n   872→\\n   873→import (\\n   874→\\t\\\"io\\\"\\n   875→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n   876→\\n   877→\\t\\\"github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent\\\"\\n   878→)\\n   879→\\n   880→const (\\n   881→\\tHookNameSessionStart = \\\"session-start\\\"\\n   882→\\tHookNameSessionEnd   = \\\"session-end\\\"\\n   883→\\tHookNamePromptSubmit = \\\"prompt-submit\\\"\\n   884→\\tHookNameResponse     = \\\"response\\\"\\n   885→)\\n   886→\\n   887→func (a *YourAgent) HookNames() []string {\\n   888→\\treturn []string{\\n   889→\\t\\tHookNameSessionStart,\\n   890→\\t\\tHookNameSessionEnd,\\n   891→\\t\\tHookNamePromptSubmit,\\n   892→\\t\\tHookNameResponse,\\n   893→\\t}\\n   894→}\\n   895→\\n   896→func (a *YourAgent) ParseHookEvent(hookName string, stdin io.Reader) (*agent.Event, error) {\\n   897→\\tswitch hookName {\\n   898→\\tcase HookNameSessionStart:\\n   899→\\t\\traw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[sessionInfoRaw](stdin)\\n   900→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   901→\\t\\t\\treturn nil, err\\n   902→\\t\\t}\\n   903→\\t\\treturn &agent.Event{\\n   904→\\t\\t\\tType:       agent.SessionStart,\\n   905→\\t\\t\\tSessionID:  raw.SessionID,\\n   906→\\t\\t\\tSessionRef: raw.TranscriptPath,\\n   907→\\t\\t\\tTimestamp:  time.Now(),\\n   908→\\t\\t}, nil\\n   909→\\n   910→\\tcase HookNamePromptSubmit:\\n   911→\\t\\traw, err := agent.ReadAndParseHookInput[promptInputRaw](stdin)\\n   912→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   913→\\t\\t\\treturn nil, err\\n   914→\\t\\t}\\n   915→\\t\\treturn &agent.Event{\\n   916→\\t\\t\\tType:       agent.TurnStart,\\n   917→\\t\\t\\tSessionID:  raw